org.team5940.robot_core.modules.ownable

Interface OwnableModule

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Module
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    MotorSetModule, PistonModule, ProcedureModule, ShifterModule, TankDrivetrainModule, TestableMotorSetModule
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractOwnableModule, AbstractProcedureModule, AggregateProcedureModule, CANTalonMotorSetModule, ContinuousSelectableProcedureModule, DoubleSolenoidPistonModule, DoubleSolenoidShifterModule, MultipleTestRunnerProcedureModule, SelectableMJPEGStreamerModule, SimpleTankDrivetrainModule, SingleShotSelectableProcedureModule, TestableCANTalonMotorSetModule

    public interface OwnableModule
extends Module
    This extension of Module that provides an interface to lock access to a Module to a particular, executing (.isAlive() is true) Thread. This is useful to preventing unintentional concurrent usage, particularly of actuators. Any ownable extended dependencies of an OwnableModule also need to be acquired.

      • isOwnedBy

        boolean isOwnedBy(java.lang.Thread t)
        This method determines whether this is currently owned by Thread t. Should return true if t == null and this is not owned. If the owner of this died, it is not owned.
        Parameters:
        t - The Thread to check ownership for.
        Returns:
        true if t == the Thread that owns this (or t == null and this is not owned), false otherwise.

        boolean acquireOwnershipFor(java.lang.Thread t,

        Acquires ownership of this for t if: (no Thread currently owns this, or force == true), and t doesn't already own this. Returns the results of this.isOwnedBy(t). Note: t can be null if you are attempting to force ownership relinquishing.
        Parameters:
        t - The Thread to acquire ownership for.
        force - Whether to force the ownership of this by t.

        true if t owns this, false otherwise.
